column13: First of all we analyze the header:
00:    This byte indicates it is an AM message
FF FF: These two bytes are the Destination address (FF FF indicates broadcast)
00 42: Source address, this indicates address of last mote before sink node. As this is a one hop application, it is also the Origin of the message
0A:    Length in bytes of the payload. 0A indicates that the payload of the message is has 10 bytes
01:    Handler id, configurable, permits identifying the type of message received. In this case we know it corresponds to a TestCM5000_AM_ID message
And the rest of the message is the Payload, the actual data of the message.
